Controls how many items can stack in one inventory slot.
Can be set per-item or globally.
Default Rust stack sizes vary by item type.

Examples: 1000, 5000, 10000

The shortname of a Rust item. Shortnames are lowercase identifiers with dots or underscores (e.g., "rifle.ak", "box.wooden.large").

Examples: rifle.ak, campfire, wood

A human-readable name. Can be an item display name, player name, or custom identifier. For items, this is usually the display name shown to players.

Examples: Assault Rifle, Camp Fire, Wood

A multiplier that affects rates, speeds, or amounts. • 1.0 = normal (100%, no change)
• 2.0 = double (200%, 2x effect)
• 0.5 = half (50%, 0.5x effect)

Used for gathering rates, craft speeds, etc.

Examples: 0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 5.0

The category an item belongs to (e.g., "Weapon", "Resource", "Medical", "Food", "Construction"). Common categories: Weapon, Resource, Medical, Food, Construction, Tool, Attire, Ammunition

Examples: Weapon, Resource, Medical, Food, Construction

Array of item shortnames. Each entry should be a valid Rust item shortname.

Examples: rifle.ak, campfire
